    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The borough council has allowed itself to be persuaded that a statue would be a fitting tribute to Albert Einstein, among the town's most famous residents. (At first, some people thought that the gesture would have offended Einstein, a determinedly modest man.)</p>
        <p>The council voted last week to look for a site for the statue. Now Dr. Melvin Benarde, a prime local backer of the project, is looking for money. He thinks it will take about $300,000.</p>
      </block>
